Modul htl.steyr.javafx_minesweeper_tplatzer
Package htl.steyr.javafx_minesweeper_tplatzer.model

Klasse UserData

java.lang.Object
htl.steyr.javafx_minesweeper_tplatzer.model.UserData
Alle implementierten Schnittstellen:
Serializable
public class UserData extends Object implements Serializable
Represents user data for the Minesweeper game, including username and best times for different difficulties.

This class implements Serializable to allow user data to be saved and loaded.

  • Konstruktordetails

    • UserData

      public UserData()
      Constructs a new UserData instance with default values.

      Initializes the user's game data with default best times and a default username. This constructor is typically used to create a new user profile with no prior game data.

      Default values:

      • beginnerBestTime: Integer.MAX_VALUE (indicating no recorded time)
      • advancedBestTime: Integer.MAX_VALUE (indicating no recorded time)
      • proBestTime: Integer.MAX_VALUE (indicating no recorded time)
      • username: "Default_Username"

    • UserData

      public UserData(String username)
      Constructs a new UserData instance with the specified username.

      Initializes the user's game data with default best times and the provided username. This constructor is typically used to create a user profile with a custom username.

      Default values:

      • beginnerBestTime: Integer.MAX_VALUE (indicating no recorded time)
      • advancedBestTime: Integer.MAX_VALUE (indicating no recorded time)
      • proBestTime: Integer.MAX_VALUE (indicating no recorded time)
      Parameter:
      username - The username to associate with this user data.
